<subSubSection id="C3776556EFDC3AB8FF78FAFFFE5DF9BF" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEFDC3AB8FF78FAFFFE5DF9BF" blockId="141.[136,778,1227,1662]" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEFDC3AB8FF78FAFFFEEFFA8A" bold="true" box="[189,298,1329,1355]" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Remarks</emphasis>
. The female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEFDC3AB8FE3FFAFCFD4AFA8A" authorityName="Buchholz" authorityYear="1869" box="[506,655,1329,1356]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Notopterophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEFDC3AB8FE3FFAFCFDC8FA8A" box="[506,525,1330,1355]" italics="true" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEFDC3AB8FDE7FAFFFD4AFA8A" box="[546,655,1329,1355]" italics="true" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has short filiform processes on the dorsal wings of the pedigerous somites. There are 3 filiform processes on the dorsal wing of first pedigerous somite, two processes on each wing of the second and third pedigerous somites, and a single process on the wing of the fourth pedigerous somite (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEFDC3AB8FF55FA33FE91F9D9" author="Giesbrecht, W." box="[144,340,1533,1560]" journalOrPublisher="Mittheilungen aus der Zoologischen Station zu Neapel" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" pagination="293 - 372" part="3" refId="ref328092" refString="Giesbrecht, W. (1882) BeitragezurKenntniseinigerNotodelphyiden. Mittheilungen aus der Zoologischen Station zu Neapel, 3, 293 - 372, pls. 22 - 24." title="BeitragezurKenntniseinigerNotodelphyiden" type="journal article" year="1882">Giesbrecht, 1882</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEFDC3AB8FEA4FA33FD8DF9D9" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[353,584,1533,1560]" journalOrPublisher="Pubblicazioni della Stazione Zoologica di Napoli" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" pagination="373 - 451" part="34" refId="ref329106" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1965) Notodelphyid copepods from the vicinity of Naples. Pubblicazioni della Stazione Zoologica di Napoli, 34, 373 - 451." title="Notodelphyid copepods from the vicinity of Naples" type="journal article" year="1965">
Illg &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49A9F83FEFDC3AB8FE68FA33FDC4F9D6" box="[429,513,1533,1559]" country="United Kingdom" name="Dudley" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Dudley</collectingRegion>
, 1965
</bibRefCitation>
). However, other studies have indicated that these processes are sometimes absent (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CEFDC3AB8FED4F98FFE02F99D" author="Buchholz, R." box="[273,455,1601,1628]" journalOrPublisher="Zeitschrift f ̡ r wissenschaftliche Zoologie" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" pagination="99 - 155" part="19" refId="ref327368" refString="Buchholz, R. (1869) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der innerhalb der Ascidien lebenden parasitischen Crustaceen des Mittelmeeres. Zeitschrift f ̡ r wissenschaftliche Zoologie, 19, 99 - 155, pls. 5 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 53715" title="Beitrage zur Kenntniss der innerhalb der Ascidien lebenden parasitischen Crustaceen des Mittelmeeres" type="journal article" year="1869">Buchholz, 1869</bibRefCitation>
), or present only on some of the wings (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFDC3AB8FEC6F9ADFE4EF9BF" box="[259,395,1635,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 92" captionStartId="140.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[245,1338,207,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-21@140.[204,1383,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 92. Habitus of three species of Notopterophorus. A, female N. auritus (Thorell, 1859), right; B, C, female N. elongatus Buchholz, 1869, right and dorsal; D, E, female N. papilio Hesse, 1864, right and ventral. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591426/files/figure.png" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Fig. 92B, C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
